When I work with Python NumPy, I often encounter use-cases
which require that I write a NumPy Array to a CSV file.
%br/
%br/
The syntax below demonstrates creation of a simple Array and then writing it to a CSV file:

%pre
  %code.python
    import numpy as np
    col0 = [1.1, 2.2, 3.3]
    col1 = [11.1, 22.2, 33.3]
    myarray = np.array([col0, col1])
    np.savetxt('/tmp/myarray.csv', myarray, delimiter=',', fmt=('%4.3f'))

